title._content: YMCA Building in Keene New Hampshire

description._content: TITLE YMCA Building in Keene New Hampshire CREATOR French, J.A., Keene NH SUBJECT Buildings - NH - Keene Gymnasiums - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Photograph of the (old) YMCA building in Keene New Hampshire, located on West Street at the site of the old Richardson Tavern. The building was erected in 1893 and membership totaled nearly 300 with an active program of events. The building was demolished in 1961. The Ashuelot National Bank was erected on this site in 1961-62. PUBLISHER Keene Public Library and the Historical Society of Cheshire County DATE DIGITAL 20091112 DATE ORIGINAL 1889?
